09/12/2007
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- NATO's foreign ministers said on Friday (December 7th) that the Euro-Atlantic integration of the Western Balkans depends on their good relations. 
According to the communiquÃ© adopted in the end of the NATO ministerial meeting in Brussels on Friday, the Euro-Atlantic integration of Albania, Macedonia and Croatia depends on the countries' regional co-operation, good relations and finding mutually acceptable solutions to all pending issues. 
(Naftemporiki, ANA-MPA - 08/12/07)
